        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When you look at Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Abstract, it does things like this in the _connect() method :\n{code}\nif (!extension_loaded('pdo')) {\n            \/**\n             * @see Zend_Db_Adapter_Exception\n             *\/\n            require_once 'Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Exception.php';\n            throw new Zend_Db_Adapter_Exception('The PDO extension is required for this adapter but the extension is not loaded');\n        }\n{code}\n\nHowever, when you look at the setFetchMode() method, it uses the PDO class without checking for the PDO extention presence which can lead to a \"PDO class not found\" bug.\nSo I suggest to add a check for the PDO extension in that method too (no more methods need that)\n"
        },
